This paper deals with quantization of deep neural networks for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The method proposed in the paper involves correcting biases in the error introduced during quantization, which is a technique that could also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community. The paper also mentions the use of activation functions, which are a fundamental concept in neural networks and could be of interest to the neural networks (cs.NE) community. Finally, the paper involves optimizing the weight ranges in the network, which could be seen as a form of data preprocessing and could be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) community.
